task.summary: [maven] The pathetic joke that is called "surefire" is unable to handle Assumptions; they are reported as failing tests. In addition it does not properly handle tests annotated with a @Category: it aborts then the category class cannot be loaded. To solve I renamed test classes that will fail (because they need a database, which we do not have yet) to the form *Db*, so that I can ignore them by name. Sigh.
